abstract: Andy Murray defeats Donald Young to win Thailand Open tennis tournament; other tennis developments noted.
snippet: Fourth-ranked Andy Murray of Britain claimed his 19th career title in beating Donald Young of the United States, 6-2, 6-0, in the final of the Thailand Open on Sunday in Bangkok.
lead_paragraph: Fourth-ranked Andy Murray of Britain claimed his 19th career title in beating Donald Young of the United States, 6-2, 6-0, in the final of the Thailand Open on Sunday in Bangkok.
